	(5954, 'Hmmm, this one looks like something that would be better off as a windchime. Take notes class... This is NOT what you want to summon in the heat of battle.', 'Hmmm, this one looks like something that would be better off as a windchime. Take notes class... This is NOT what you want to summon in the heat of battle.', 0, 0, 0, 94, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
	(5955, 'What could be taking so long?', '', 0, 0, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
	(5956, 'How long can it take to pick a handful of weeds?', '', 0, 0, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
	(5957, 'At this rate I could have gathered them myself!', '', 0, 0, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
	(5958, 'If you want something done right, do it yourself!', '', 0, 0, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
	(5959, 'As if I had all eternity.', '', 0, 0, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
	(5960, 'Ah, this must be him now... no?  Bah!', '', 0, 0, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
	(5961, 'Maybe I should have just bought some off of Faruza?', '', 0, 0, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
	(5962, 'I had to go and requisition an Abomination... an Abomination!', '', 0, 0, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
	(5963, '', 'The body is that of a female orc warrior.$B$BIt is clear that she died in battle, probably against the quilboar in the area.', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
	(5964, 'I inspect the body further.', 'I inspect the body further.', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
	(5965, '', 'You turn the body over and see the marks from blades and spells upon the deceased orc--her armor all but destroyed, her hair matted to her face.$B$BBased on Mankrik\'s description of her, there is no doubt in your mind that this was his wife.$B$BHe will be upset by the news, but you are sure he should know the truth.', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
	(5966, 'Start running!', 'Start running!', 0, 0, 3, 25, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
	(5967, 'Bring it on!', 'Bring it on!', 0, 0, 3, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
	(5968, 'Do not push me, or I will impale you on my horns!', 'Do not push me, or I will impale you on my horns!', 0, 0, 3, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
	(5969, 'Welcome to the Crossroads, $c. My name is Thork--I lead the defenses here in the name of the Warchief.$B$BPlease, feel free to make yourself at home. As long as you mind your business, no one should have any problem with you taking up some space.$B$BThere are many threats to our safety here. If you\'ve already become familiar with the lay of the land, speak to the others here--perhaps they have tasks for you to do.', '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
	(5970, '<Goretooth spits.>$B$BI am a warrior of the Horde, $n. It fills me with rage to know that our enemies sit in a fortress, less than a day\'s ride from Kargath, plotting against us.$B$BHow I long to break free from the bonds of duty and destroy them all in the name of the Warchief.$B$BAlas, we all have roles we must fulfill.\n', '', 0, 0, 0, 14, 5, 1, 0, 0, 0),
	(5971, 'What roles?', 'What roles?', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
	(5972, 'Truly, I envy you: To battle in the name of the Horde, at the forefront of conflict. Mine is a job of command.$B$BCertainly, in my youth, I lived out the dreams that make my old age bearable. I now revel in the glory of victory, the bitter taste of defeat - all through the soldiers I command.\n', '', 0, 0, 0, 1, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0),
	(5973, 'Dreams?', 'Dreams?', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
	(5974, 'I dream, $n... oh yes, I dream. In my dreams I die a thousand times in a thousand different ways. Some would call dreams such as mine nightmares. NOT I! In dreams I die in the thick of battle. For each single death of my own, ten thousand enemies of the Horde fall before me. It is glorious!', '', 0, 0, 0, 1, 1, 5, 0, 0, 0),
	(5975, 'I pray for such things.', 'I pray for such things.', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
	(5976, 'Aye, I could tell just by looking at you, $n. You remind me very much of myself as a young warrior of the Horde.$B$BYou will undoubtedly go far in life and even further in death.$B$B<Goretooth salutes.>', '', 0, 0, 0, 1, 1, 66, 0, 0, 0),
	(5977, 'I do not deserve such praise, Warlord Goretooth.', 'I do not deserve such praise, Warlord Goretooth.', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
	(5978, 'And modest too... Perhaps it is your time, then, $n.$B$BAre you prepared to enter the fortress of the Blackrock orcs? To wreak havoc? To tear asunder the foundation of the mountain citadel?', '', 0, 0, 0, 25, 6, 6, 0, 0, 0),
	(5979, 'Sir! Until my body ceases to function!', 'Sir! Until my body ceases to function!', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
	(5980, 'I did not doubt you for even one second, $n.$B$BHere are your orders, $n. I know that you will not let me down.\n', '', 0, 0, 0, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
	(5981, 'Yes, sir. Thank you, sir!', 'Yes, sir. Thank you, sir!', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
	(5982, '%s bows before Krang Stonehoof', '%s bows before Krang Stonehoof', 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
	(5983, 'Ah a visitor! Must be an adventurer, we don\'t get many tourists down this way. Grab a chair and a drink, make yourself comfortable. Say, you look like you have some meat on your bones. You thinkin about competing in the cage matches?', 'Ah a visitor! Must be an adventurer, we don\'t get many tourists down this way. Grab a chair and a drink, make yourself comfortable. Say, you look like you have some meat on your bones. You thinkin about competing in the cage matches?', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
	(5984, '%s attacks the pike!', '', 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
	(5985, '%s destroys the pike!', '', 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
	(5986, '%s and Raider Kerr let their wolves rest a bit and drink...', '', 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
	(5987, '%s and Raider Kerr charge into battle...', '', 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
	(5988, '%s takes aim...', '', 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
	(5989, 'Greetings, young $c.', '', 0, 0, 0, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
	(5990, 'Hello, Eitrigg. I bring news from Blackrock Spire.', 'Hello, Eitrigg. I bring news from Blackrock Spire.', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
	(5991, 'Rend, son of Blackhand: Impotent chieftain of the Blackrock clan. A more stubborn bastard does not exist.$B$BAt the end of the second War, Rend and his brother, Maim, fled to find sanctuary within the mountainous stronghold of Blackrock Spire. It was there that Rend declared himself Warchief of the weakened Blackrock clan.', '', 0, 0, 0, 1, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0),
	(5992, 'There is only one Warchief, Eitrigg!', 'There is only one Warchief, Eitrigg!', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
	(5993, 'Yes, young one, you need not convince me of such things, the Warchief and I have much history. Your dedication, however, is noted.$B$BAs I was saying, Rend had found a new home for his people, and I was among those who would wearily follow.$B$BFrom one conflict arose others... countless others. It was in those battles for Blackrock Spire between the Blackrock clan and the Dark Iron dwarves that my sons were both slain. It was then that I realized my time among the Blackrock clan had come to an end.', '', 0, 0, 0, 1, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0),
	(5994, 'What do you mean?', 'What do you mean?', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
	(5995, 'I left. I would not remain with the Blackrock. No, the deaths of my children would not be in vain. I would not serve under an inept, power hungry maniac such as Rend.$B$BI took shelter in the woods of Lordaeron, living as a hermit near Hearthglen.', '', 0, 0, 0, 1, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0),
	(5996, 'Hearthglen?? But...\n', 'Hearthglen?? But...\n', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
	(5997, '<Eitrigg laughs.>$B$BYoung one, the world has not always been in such disarray. It was a time before the Scourge had sacked the land. Before those parts of Lordaeron were known as the Plaguelands.$B$BIt was there that Thrall rescued me from death and it was then that I joined the new Horde... but I digress. This is a story for another time. Yes, another time... Perhaps...', '', 0, 0, 0, 11, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0),
	(5998, 'I will take you up on that offer, Eitrigg.', 'I will take you up on that offer, Eitrigg.', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
	(5999, 'I\'m certain you will. Perhaps one day you could deliver a message to an old friend of mine. I hear he still wanders those woods.$B$B<Eitrigg bows his head for a moment, as if in prayer.>$B$BSo Rend, yes... Rend and his brother Maim ruled the Spire, in constant conflict with the Dark Iron dwarves. They managed to displace the dwarves in the upper portion of the city, but only after the dragons came and only after the death of Maim.', '', 0, 0, 0, 1, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0),
	(6000, 'Ah, so that is how they pushed the Dark Iron to the lower parts of the Spire.', 'Ah, so that is how they pushed the Dark Iron to the lower parts of the Spire.', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
	(6001, 'Indeed. Nefarian, brood of Deathwing, rules the Spire now. Rend is under the command of the dragon.$B$BIf only you could somehow manage to pass through the Halls of Ascension.$B$B<Eitrigg sighs.>$B$BAlas, only those deemed worthy by the black flight earn privilege to ascend.\n', '', 0, 0, 0, 1, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0),
	(6002, 'Perhaps there exists a way?', 'Perhaps there exists a way?', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
	(6003, 'Perhaps. Go now, young one. Seek council with the Warchief. He will surely wish to know of your discovery.', '', 0, 0, 0, 1, 25, 0, 0, 0, 0),
	(6004, 'As you wish, Eitrigg.', 'As you wish, Eitrigg.', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
	(6005, 'Hulfnar!  Thontek!  Stand and address me.', 'Hulfnar!  Thontek!  Stand and address me.', 0, 0, 3, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
	(6006, 'It\'s 428,000 degrees Kraklenheit... What\'s happening, hot stuff!?', '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
	(6007, 'DING! 428,000 degrees Kraklenheit, exactly! Well, approximately. Almost. Somewhere around there...', '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
	(6008, 'Measuring by Kraklenheit, it is 428,000 degrees! That\'s Krakley!', '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
	(6009, '18 degrees Kraklenheit. It\'s kind of cold, actually...', '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
	(6010, 'It\'s 40 degrees Kraklenheit. Can you feel the heat? No? I really couldn\'t either.', '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
	(6011, 'Wow, it\'s 3 degrees Kraklenheit. Keep looking.', '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
	(6012, 'The stake is covered with the remnants of those foolish enough to anger the Warchief.', '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
	(6013, 'Honor your heroes! On this day, they have dealt a great blow against one of our most hated enemies! The false Warchief, Rend Blackhand, has fallen!', '', 6, 0, 0, 22, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
	(6014, 'Be bathed in my power! Drink in my might! Battle for the glory of the Horde!', '', 6, 0, 0, 22, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
	(6015, 'Be bathed in the power of the Warchief! Drink in his might! Battle for the glory of the Horde!', '', 6, 0, 0, 22, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
	(6016, 'The Valley of Trials will temper even the weakest into a warrior worthy to join the Horde. Those who cannot rise to its tests will be left to bake in the scorching desert sun.', '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
	(6017, 'Place Rend\'s head on the stake.', 'Place Rend\'s head on the stake.', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
	(6018, '', 'Hello there, $N.  I am known as Chronormu, but you may call me Chromie.  I am comfortable with such familiarity.$B$BNow - how did I know your name, you ask?  I am one of the bronze dragonflight, forever attuned to the ebb and flow of time.  You could say that we have met before.  To that end, we shall also meet again.$B$BI hope that my choice of visual demeanor does not disturb you; while I might be charged to be a sentry of sorrowful places, I choose not to drown in the sorrow of the locale.\n\n\n', 0, 0, 0, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
	(6019, '', 'Hello once again, $n.  I sense that the flow of time remains threatened by forces that are quite powerful indeed.  Your continued assistance is always welcomed by the bronze dragonflight.$B$BWhile the past is set in its ways, the future is always changing.  The decisions you make in the here and now help guide that change.', 0, 0, 0, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
	(6020, 'I want you both to demonstrate the techniques I have taught you for the benefit of the younger students here.  Ready...  begin!', 'I want you both to demonstrate the techniques I have taught you for the benefit of the younger students here.  Ready...  begin!', 0, 0, 3, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
	(6021, '', 'This is where I get off, suckers!', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
	(6022, '', 'Tell Lexlort if he wants the information, all he has to do is pay! Unfortunately, that means he can\'t kill me if he wants the information - since I burned the battle plans and all...', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
	(6023, '', 'Listen to your elders, $n. If you are strong of will and dedicated, there is no power you cannot control.', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
	(6024, '', 'Not all Forsaken are driven by Sylvanas\' will, $n. Some of us are driven by true power--power we earn for ourselves.', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
	(6025, 'Enough talk you two!  Commence fighting!', 'Enough talk you two!  Commence fighting!', 0, 0, 3, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
	(6026, '', 'Now\'s not a good time, $n.$B$BAre you insane?!', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
	(6027, '', 'It... is... not... the best... time, $n. I must concen... trate.', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
	(6028, '', 'Your errand must mean much, $c, to draw you so deep into the marsh...', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
	(6029, '', 'The infernal is one of the most powerful demons a warlock could hope to have at $Ghis:her; side in battle. The creature is stong, well-armored, and delivers devastating blows upon any foe. If you were to choose to put the spirit of an infernal into your weapon, you would gain some of those benefits--greater health and regeneration and the like.$B$BIf you wish to know more about felhounds, then you should speak to Wytula across from me.', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
	(6030, '', 'The felhound... a vicious creature indeed. It is not as physically strong as an infernal, but a wise warlock knows that brute force is not always the answer--if it was, you would have chosen the path of a warrior instead, wouldn\'t you?$B$BThe felhound draws upon the mana of its foes, using that and its quickness to overcome enemies. Its strength comes from the arcane and using that arcane power for its own ends.$B$BIf you wish to know more about infernals, then you should speak to Magaz across from me.', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
	(6031, 'ROOKERY MINION SPAWN DEBUG', 'ROOKERY MINION SPAWN DEBUG', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
	(6032, 'ROOKERY MINION death DEBUG', 'ROOKERY MINION death DEBUG', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
	(6033, '%s is summoned through a temporal rift!', '', 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
	(6034, '', 'Have you spoken to either of my acolytes inside the tower yet, $n? We cannot complete your orb until you\'ve done one of their tasks. Speak to them now, if you\'re ready.', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
	(6035, 'Help me kill $n!', '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
	(6036, 'Protect me from this $n! I must return to my brood.', '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
	(6037, 'Don\'t let me die!', '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
	(6038, 'Well Done!', 'Well Done!', 0, 0, 3, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
	(6039, '', '%s roars out for her mate!', 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
	(6040, '%s answers the call of Shy-Rotam.', '', 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
	(6043, 'Please, help me $g brother : sister;...$B$BI will soon pass from this world, and though I suffer I know I shall not any more once I pass.  The wildlife though, my $g brother : sister;... the wildlife suffers too, and it knows no release.  I ask for your aid with my last breaths of life.', '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
	(6045, 'Yes, I speak a language you understand $r.  We are not animals, yet most of your kind continues to treat us as such!  Our differences though pale to the tragedy that has befallen this land.  Please, put aside your differences with my kind and hear my dying plea.$B$BI came to this land to mend what I could, and now that will be for naught unless you can aid me.  I ask for such aid with my last breaths of life.', '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
	(6046, '"..."$B$BThe body of the tauren druid lies still and unmoving.  It would seem as though he has finally passed from this world to his promised great beyond.', '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
	(6061, 'None may challenge the Brotherhood!', '', 1, 5780, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
	(6062, 'And stay down!', '', 1, 5781, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
	(6063, 'Lapdogs, all of you!', '', 1, 5782, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
	(6064, 'Fools! Our cause is righteous!', '', 1, 5783, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
	(6065, 'The Brotherhood shall prevail!', '', 1, 5784, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
	(6066, 'Leaping leper gnomes! I\'ve been stuck in there for months. Thanks, gang.', '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
	(6067, 'Who dares step into my domain!  Come!  Come, and be consumed!', '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
	(6068, 'Ever vigilant in their protection of the natural world, the druids are guided by Arch Druid Fandral Staghelm who resides in the Cenarion Enclave.  You will find him and the other Druid trainers in the northern section of Darnassus.', 'Ever vigilant in their protection of the natural world, the druids are guided by Arch Druid Fandral Staghelm who resides in the Cenarion Enclave.  You will find him and the other Druid trainers in the northern section of Darnassus.', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
	(6069, 'I am an officer of the city, working in the capacity of the Undercity\'s census.  Since our liberation from the Scourge, we have tried to keep an accurate track of our city\'s populace.  Through arcane methods and sharpened mental discipline, I am able to access these records.  If you have business with me accordingly, please proceed.  You should know if you do, at any rate.', '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
	(6070, 'The Warchief has instructed me to study all kinds of weapons and armor. He has sent me here to the hub of both the tauren and orc cultures in the Barrens to meet as many travelers as possible, and to learn about the cultures of the Barrens.$B$BHe feels there\'s something to be learned from even the most pathetic of cultures... like the quilboar or centaur.', '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
	(6071, 'You surrendered.  I win.', 'You surrendered.  I win.', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
	(6072, 'Now that\'s a War Stomp!  Good job!', 'Now that\'s a War Stomp!  Good job!', 0, 0, 3, 21, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
	(6073, 'That\'s how it\'s done class!  You better be paying attention!', 'That\'s how it\'s done class!  You better be paying attention!', 0, 0, 3, 21, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
	(6074, 'Now that\'s putting your hoof down!', 'Now that\'s putting your hoof down!', 0, 0, 3, 21, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
	(6075, 'You! $R! Come here. <snort>$B$BTime is short, and my end <snort> is near. Mangletooth shall win; you will see. <snort>$B$BMy capture can still aid <snort> my people. The Razormane tribe is more powerful than the Bristlebacks!$B$BThe Horde looks to find out who leads the raids on their people. You <snort> shall aid Mangletooth in return for the information only I know. Mangletooth can help you! <snort> But you must help Mangletooth.', '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
	(6076, 'Welcome to Stormwind!  I am one of the city\'s officers, aiding the citizenry of the city through our census bureau.  If you are in need of locating someone specific, then I might be able to assist you.  Through arcane methods and sharpened mental discipline, I am able to access these records.$B$BIf you have business with me, then please proceed!', '', 0, 0, 0, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
	(6077, 'My hatred is strong <snort>, but the time is right to tell you a tale, $r.$B$BLong ago a battle took place between gods. Agamaggan, our great boar god, fell to the earth after being defeated in the War of the Ancients, his blood raining down and his bones torn asunder. <snort>$B$BGreat thorns reached up out of the earth where his blood touched the ground, and his skull adorns one of the caverns to the south.', '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
	(6078, 'Whew... I need a smoke and the touch of a fine gnomish woman - not particularly in that order!$B$BI\'ve been stuck inside the belly of that thing for months! What day is it anyway? Ah, nevermind. All that matters is that I\'m finally out.$B$BWOOO HOOO!', '', 0, 0, 0, 1, 5, 4, 0, 0, 0),
	(6079, 'How the hell did you get in there to begin with?\n', 'How the hell did you get in there to begin with?\n', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
	(6080, 'How?? Well, it\'s a long story.', '', 0, 0, 0, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
	(6081, 'I\'m all ears.', 'I\'m all ears.', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
	(6082, 'Alrighty then! So I was down at the lava pits of the Molten Span, testing out my lava suit. Everything was going great. I was even able to swim around in that stuff without suffering a single injury!$B$BSo there I am, minding my own business, doing a few backstrokes, when out of nowhere this thing swallows me up whole! Had it not been for my lava suit and built in food pellet dispenser, I would have been done for!', '', 0, 0, 0, 1, 1, 5, 0, 0, 0),
	(6083, 'So let me get this straight. You were swimming, nay, doing backstrokes in molten lava with this... this lava suit of yours? Yes? And out of nowhere, this here beast swallowed you whole? ', 'So let me get this straight. You were swimming, nay, doing backstrokes in molten lava with this... this lava suit of yours? Yes? And out of nowhere, this here beast swallowed you whole? ', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
	(6084, 'Say, I sense a measure of disbelief in your voice - but yes, that\'s how it happened.', '', 0, 0, 0, 1, 25, 0, 0, 0, 0),
	(6085, 'I must know something: How did you go to the bathroom with that thing on?', 'I must know something: How did you go to the bathroom with that thing on? ', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
	(6086, 'I\'m not out of the belly of this beast for more than two minutes and someone is already asking me about my bathroom behavior??? $G Mister:Missy;, I\'d have smacked you silly for that question had you not been the one to rescue me!$B$BAnyhow! I\'m grateful for the assistance. Maybe I can pay you back?', '', 0, 0, 0, 6, 1, 6, 0, 0, 0),
	(6087, 'Oh?', 'Oh?', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
	(6088, 'Well, maybe \'pay\' isn\'t the best word to use. See, when I was stuck in the belly of that thing, I got to thinking:$B$BThis creature lives in hot, flaming magma and yet it doesn\'t take a lick of damage from the fire!$B$BIf only I could find a pristine hide from one of these beasts. I could take it back to my dear friend, Malyfous Darkhammer, in Everlook. If anyone could do anything with the hide of a beast like this, it would be him. \n', '', 0, 0, 0, 1, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0),
	(6089, 'I\'ll consider that the next time I run into one of these things.', 'I\'ll consider that the next time I run into one of these things.', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
