	(10045, 'Unlike most ogres, I do know what an outhouse is for - giving you a swirlie.  Now beat it.', '', 0, 0, 0, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
	(10046, 'I have long known you\'d seek me out, $N.$B$BEvery sentient being in this world is driven by the choices they make.  Choices begat further choices, and these in turn make someone who they are.  This is where your fortune is drawn from - who you are, and the choices you make.$B$BAre you ready to discover where your fortune lies?', '', 0, 0, 0, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
	(10047, 'I am ready to discover where my fortune lies!', 'I am ready to discover where my fortune lies!', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
	(10048, 'Very well then...$B$BYou have been tasked by your liege to guard his fields of corn from poachers and thieves.  One night on patrol, you stumble across a haggard man in thread-bare clothing stealing corn from the field.  You quickly confront him, and he immediately begs for his life.  He claims he is stealing the corn to feed his family since the lord of the land - your liege - demands too much in taxes.  Your liege is indeed known for his harsh taxes throughout the land.$B$BMake your choice.\n', '', 0, 0, 0, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
	(10049, 'I slay the man on the spot as my liege would expect me to do, as he is nothing more than a thief and a liar.', 'I slay the man on the spot as my liege would expect me to do, as he is nothing more than a thief and a liar.', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
	(10050, 'I turn over the man to my liege for punishment, as he has broken the law of the land and it is my sworn duty to enforce it.', 'I turn over the man to my liege for punishment, as he has broken the law of the land and it is my sworn duty to enforce it.', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
	(10051, 'I confiscate the corn he has stolen, warn him that stealing is a path towards doom and destruction, but I let him go to return to his family.', 'I confiscate the corn he has stolen, warn him that stealing is a path towards doom and destruction, but I let him go to return to his family.', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
	(10052, 'I allow the man to take enough corn to feed his family for a couple of days, encouraging him to leave the land.', 'I allow the man to take enough corn to feed his family for a couple of days, encouraging him to leave the land.', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
	(10053, 'Your next choice awaits.$B$BYou are the sworn executioner for your liege.  A man has been sent to you for execution as a traitor of the liege and your people.  You know this individual as a close, virtuous friend who mysteriously vanished one day.  You also know that the man\'s crimes for which he was convicted supposedly caused the deaths of many innocent civilians.  Upon seeing you he begs for his life, claiming he was framed by a higher authority.$B$BMake your choice.\n\n', '', 0, 0, 0, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
