	(12471, 'Did you think that your betrayal would be forgotten? Lost in the carefully planned cover up of my death? Blood of my blood, the blade felt your cruelty long after my heart had stopped beating. And in death, I knew what you had done. But now, the chains of Kel\'Thuzad hold me no more. I come to serve justice. I AM ASHBRINGER.\n', '', 0, 0, 0, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
